{{for|the radio station|The Squeaky Wheel}}

[[Image:Squeakywheellogo.png|thumb|Squeaky Wheel]]

'''Squeaky Wheel''' '''Film & Media Art Center''' is an artist-run, non-profit, media arts center based in [[Buffalo, New York]].<ref name=Dabkowski>{{cite web|last1=Dabkowski|first1=Colin|title=Squeaky Wheel leaves behind speakeasy vibe in move to Market Arcade|url=http://www.buffalonews.com/gusto/art/squeaky-wheel-leaves-behind-speakeasy-vibe-in-move-to-market-arcade-20141129|website=Buffalo News|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=Dab2>{{cite web|last1=Dabkowski|first1=Colin|title=A Closer Look: The new Squeaky Wheel|url=http://buffalo.com/2015/03/18/featured/a-closer-look-the-new-squeaky-wheel/|website=The Buffalo News|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=dillman>{{cite web|last1=Dillman|first1=Tina|title=Squeaky Wheel at 30: Realizing the past while being present in the now|url=http://www.dailypublic.com/articles/12092014/squeaky-wheel-30-realizing-past-while-being-present-now|website=The Public|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref> Founded in 1985, the organization provides the Western New York region with low-cost media equipment rentals, media arts education for youth and adults, residencies for artists and researchers, and exhibitions, screenings, and other public programming.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://squeaky.org/mission/|title=Mission|date=2016-11-22|work=Squeaky Wheel Film & Media Art Center|access-date=2018-02-12|language=en-US}}</ref>

